text.p: Relatively high T c (∼ 20 K) is maintained even in a F-overdoped regime (x ∼ 0.2).

In these compounds, protons act as H − as well as F − , and O 2− can be replaced with H − up to x ∼ 0.6. In the H-overdoped regime (x ≥ 0.2), LaFeAsO 1−x H x undergoes a second superconducting state as shown in Fig. 1(a).
